# Pacelab Tech Stack

Use these exact packages and tools for everything you build. Never suggest alternatives unless a package is incompatible with Expo bare workflow.

## Frontend
- **React Native** with **Expo** (bare workflow)
- **TypeScript** strict mode
- **Zustand** for global state management
- **React Navigation** for all navigation (tab + stack + bottom sheet modals)
- **Mapbox GL** for route maps with pace/HR heatmap overlay
- **Victory Native XL** for all charts and graphs
- **expo-location** for GPS run tracking
- **expo-document-picker** for GPX file import
- **fast-xml-parser** for GPX file parsing
- **react-native-background-fetch** for background sync
- **react-native-health** for Apple HealthKit

## Backend
- **Supabase** for auth, database, and file storage
- **Supabase Edge Functions** for server-side processing

## AI
- **Groq Llama 3.3 70B**: coach chat, plan builder, daily briefings, post-run summaries, Strava/training analysis

## External APIs
- **Strava API v3** — OAuth, history import, webhook sync
- **Garmin Health API** — wellness data
- **Apple HealthKit** — Apple Watch data
- **Mapbox** — maps
- **OpenWeather API** — weather context

## App identity
- **App name:** Pacelab
- **Bundle ID:** com.benny.pacelab
- **Design:** Light theme, Apple HIG style (as already established)
